div.p:
that—
To unconditionally accept as noncontraband all merchandise not universally accepted or described in their rules as such would open the door to contractors in Japan to import
foodstuffs and other merchandise without limit for account of the Japanese Government—that is, on account of or in destination of the enemy—that the Russian Government could not but consider as contraband a cargo of flour consigned to a port at which was quartered a large body of troops, and that extending this principle the ultimate destination of the cargo had to be taken into consideration although its direct consignment might be to a merchant in an open port;
